SIMPLE: outbrave
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Outbrave
<hw>Out*brave"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
excel in bravery or in insolence; to defy with superior courage or
audacity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To excel in magnificence or comeliness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The basest weed <qex>outbraves</qex> his dignity.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outbray</ent>⟦br⟧
